bered stanza—tar-scent, rain on tiles, and a voice laughing because you dared the highest beam—and it settles in your chest like a warm stone. The city gains a crate of gentling light and a promise that more can be made, the Collegium files a letter of thanks that opens a door two hallways hence, and the night that follows is quieter by a chorus you cannot hear until you notice what is not happening.\"},\n        {\"id\": \"C2\", \"title\": \"Pursue the Walking Memory\", \"text\": \"When the laughter you forgot steps across the shade like a tide-line shape and looks back, you follow it, measuring your breaths against Jaya’s counts until the numbers blur into a hum and the hum becomes a path. You keep to roots that remember sunlight, but the Orchard bends distance into a ripple and you find yourself two steps deeper, where leaves sip starlight before it reaches the ground and direction tastes sweet and wrong on your tongue. You see the figure of the kindness you lost—hands powdered with rope dust, eyes bright with dare and care—and you ask it to stop, which it does not, not at first, not until you say the name you think might be right, voice shaking like a line under strain. You cut sap carefully, faster than is wise and slower than your hunger, and you carry it back with pockets of darkness clinging to the seams of your thoughts like burrs after a fen-walk. You feel Lysa’s patience shiver when she senses the line you crossed, and you feel the Night Orchard’s gaze settle like dew on your shoulders, cool and kind up to the point that it is not.\", \"outcome\": \"The lacquer you and Jaya mix is deeper, more resonant, and when it settles on the pane it hushes the Shard’s tug with a compassion that feels almost like memory soothing a fever, and Erynn breathes out as if she has been standing on tiptoe all week. The Order’s report will carry a hairline crack of concern through Lysa’s handwriting, a note about ‘exceeding the white dust’, and while no summons arrives tonight